"## Proof by contradiction\n"
"In order to prove a statement, say §0, it can often be beneficial to assume §1 and try to prove a **contradiction**. A contradiction is a compound statement that is always False regardless of the True/False values of its component parts. A prototypical example would be a statement like §2:\n"
"* if §3 is True, then the conjunction is False;\n"
"* if §4 is False, then the conjunction is still False.\n"
