#. ```
#. §8: `exact h`
#: Game.Levels.DivisionWorld.L05_division
#: Game.Levels.PrimeWorld.L04_prime
#: Game.Levels.GCDWorld.L02_GCD
msgid "The tactic §0 behaves like §1, except that named (?x) or unnamed (?_) holes in §2 that are not solved by unification with the main goal's target type are converted into new goals, using the hole's name, if any, as the goal case name.\n"
"\n"
"For example, this can be helpful for goals like §3. Instead of calling §4 multiple times we could simply use:\n"
"§5\n"
"This will generate four subgoals of the corresponding type. If we have an **Assumption** like §6, then we could use:\n"
"§7\n"
"This will generate three subgoals of the corresponding type (the would-be third goal has been cleared with §8)."
msgstr ""

