"### ❯ The §3 tactic\n"
"Although you can use the **axiom** §4 directly, it's a little easier to us the custom tactic §5. 🔍 Check out the entry for §6 in the **Tactics** tab. 👉 Our usage should look like\n"
"§7\n"
"where §8 destructures as in §9 the proposition §10."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `⊢ P ∨ Q`
#. §1: `left`
#. §2: `⊢ P`
#: Game.Levels.OrderWorld.L05_order
#: Game.Levels.OrderWorld.L05_order
msgid "If our goal is of the form §0, the tactic §1 will make our goal §2."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `«{x}» : Z`
#. §1: `«{hx}» : «{b}» = «{a}» * «{x}»`
#. §2: `«{hbc}»`
#: Game.Levels.TestWorld.L14_test
msgid "**Note:** we now have that §0 in **Objects** and §1 in **Assumptions**. 👉 Now try to desctructure the hypothesis §2."
msgstr ""

#. §0: $a,b ∈ ℤ$
#. §1: $b ∣ a$
#. §2: $0$
#. §3: $\\{ s ∈ Z ∣ 0 ≤ s ∧ ∃ q ∈ ℤ, s = a - bq \\}$
#: Game.Levels.DivisionWorld.L01_division
msgid "For all §0, if §1, then §2 is an element of the set\n"
"§3."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `intro`
#. §1: `rewrite`
#. §2: `rfl`
#. §3: `rw`
#. §4: `rewrite`
#. §5: `rfl`
#. §6: `rewrite[h]`
#. §7: `rw[h]`
#: Game.Levels.TestWorld.L01_test
msgid "We've proven our first theorem! And we've learned about the tactics §0, §1 and §2.\n"
"\n"
"### **💡 Pro-tip**\n"
"In practice, we **almost always** use the variant §3 instead of §4 since the former will automatically try to clear the goal with §5 and thereby save us a line. So instead of §6 we could have used §7 and cleared the goal. ⏮ Go back and give it a try!"
msgstr ""
